WorkItem.Description:
Some keywords, for example function, are followed by whitespace, per industry standards. Some are not, for example if, for and while.

However, the Visual Studio TypeScript formatting does format these things correctly.

Here's some code to test:

var x, i = 0, f = () => 15;
if (x = f()) { }
while (x--) { }
for (i = 0, x = f(); i < x; i++) { }
do { } while (x-- > 5);
